sources.title: Oh, Daddy!
sources.description: “Charming, funny period piece” (IMDB review quote) A musical comedy with the familiar theme of hypocritical prudes versus the younger generation. Clever comedy writing often upstages the limited-budget production numbers. The competent primary cast is headed by Leslie Henson and Frances Day. IMDB rating 5.7. Directed by Graham Cutts and Austin Melford. Released in 1935 (UK only). Complete print.

metadata.Plot: Member of a village Purity League branch find things much livelier on a trip to London.
metadata.Writer: Franz Arnold, Ernst Bach, Austin Melford
metadata.Actors: Leslie Henson, Frances Day, Robertson Hare
